author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Les Miles' fakery makes the difference: What Florida media said about LSU game
text:
Leonard Fournette got his yards, Brandon Harris had another good passing game, but in the end it was Les Miles that did in the Florida Gators.
Miles called the trick play fake field goal for the winning points in LSU's 35-28 victory against Florida and its first-year coach Jim McElwain. The Gainesville Sun's Pat Dooley said being burned by Les Miles as such officially makes McElwain an SEC coach.
Florida fell just short thanks to three plays, writes the Sun's Robbie Andreu, who also says Florida should drop the DBU boasting . Maybe LSU should also.
Edgar Thompson of the Orlando Sentinel writes that the Gators almost accomplished Mission Impossible . Here were the three things Gator fans learned.
Graham Hack of the Florida Times-Union writes LSU held off the Gators with special teams play.
5 things learned from Florida's loss to LSU, writes Anthony Chiang of the Palm Beach Post.
